An '''oxycation''' is a [[polyatomic ion]] with a [[positive charge]] that contains [[oxygen]].

==Examples==
* [[Dioxygenyl]] ion, {{chem|O|2|+}}
* [[Nitrosonium]] ion,{{chem|NO|+}}
* [[Nitronium]] ion, {{chem|NO|2|+}}
* [[Vanadyl ion]], VO<sup>2+</sup>, a very stable oxycation
* [[Uranyl]] ion, {{chem|UO|2|2+}}, all natural U<sup>6+</sup> occurs in this form
* [[Zirconyl chloride|Zirconyl]] ion,  [Zr<sub>4</sub>(OH)<sub>8</sub>]<sup>8+</sup>

See [[:Category:Oxycations|category]] for a bigger list.

